# Claude QA Hooks — CODEOWNERS
#
# When Claude creates PRs that touch these paths, GitHub will auto-request
# review from the listed owners. This ensures senior devs review:
#   - Security-sensitive code
#   - Infrastructure and auth changes
#   - Payment processing logic
#   - The QA hooks themselves
#
# Configure these handles for your team. Example:
#   @your-org/senior-devs
#   @your-org/security-team

# --- Security-sensitive paths (MUST have human review) ---
# Auth, sessions, tokens, permissions
**/auth/**                    @litsonco/senior-devs
**/middleware/auth*           @litsonco/senior-devs
**/permissions/**             @litsonco/senior-devs
**/*session*                  @litsonco/senior-devs
**/*token*                    @litsonco/senior-devs

# Payments and billing
**/payments/**                @litsonco/senior-devs
**/billing/**                 @litsonco/senior-devs
**/stripe/**                  @litsonco/senior-devs
**/subscriptions/**           @litsonco/senior-devs

# Infrastructure and deployment
**/Dockerfile                 @litsonco/senior-devs
**/docker-compose*            @litsonco/senior-devs
**/.github/workflows/**       @litsonco/senior-devs
**/deploy/**                  @litsonco/senior-devs
**/*.tf                       @litsonco/senior-devs

# Environment and secrets
**/.env*                      @litsonco/senior-devs
**/secrets/**                 @litsonco/senior-devs

# Database migrations
**/migrations/**              @litsonco/senior-devs
**/migrate/**                 @litsonco/senior-devs

# --- QA hooks themselves ---
scripts/**                    @litsonco/senior-devs
install.sh                    @litsonco/senior-devs
